What is ReentrantLock in Java?,A lock that allows threads to re-enter the same lock multiple times.
ReentrantLock example,Lock lock = new ReentrantLock(); lock.lock(); try{...} finally{lock.unlock();}
What is Executor framework?,It provides a high-level API for managing threads using ThreadPool.
ExecutorService example,ExecutorService ex = Executors.newFixedThreadPool(2); ex.execute(new Task()); ex.shutdown();
Callable and Future example,Future<Integer> f = ex.submit(() -> 10); int res = f.get();
SingleThreadExecutor example,ExecutorService ex = Executors.newSingleThreadExecutor(); ex.execute(task); ex.shutdown();
What is CountDownLatch?,A synchronization aid that allows threads to wait until a set of operations complete.
CountDownLatch example,CountDownLatch latch = new CountDownLatch(3); latch.countDown(); latch.await();
What is Semaphore?,Semaphore controls number of threads accessing a resource.
Semaphore example,Semaphore sem = new Semaphore(2); sem.acquire(); sem.release();
What is CyclicBarrier?,A barrier that allows threads to wait for each other to reach a common point.
CyclicBarrier example,CyclicBarrier cb = new CyclicBarrier(3); cb.await();
